SonarQube Server Installation (Ubuntu EC2)

1. Update the Server

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install Java 17

sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y

Verify Java

java -version

3. Install PostgreSQL

sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib -y

4. Create SonarQube Database and User

sudo -i -u postgres

psql

CREATE DATABASE sonarqube;
CREATE USER sonar WITH ENCRYPTED PASSWORD 'Sonar@123';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE sonarqube TO sonar;
ALTER DATABASE sonarqube OWNER TO sonar;

\q

exit

5. Download SonarQube

cd /opt

sudo wget https://binaries.sonarsource.com/Distribution/sonarqube/sonarqube-25.7.0.110598.zip

6. Install Unzip

sudo apt install unzip -y

7. Extract SonarQube

sudo unzip sonarqube-25.7.0.110598.zip

sudo mv sonarqube-25.7.0.110598 sonarqube

8. Create SonarQube User

sudo useradd -r -M -d /opt/sonarqube -s /bin/bash sonar

sudo chown -R sonar:sonar /opt/sonarqube

9. Configure Database Connection

sudo nano /opt/sonarqube/conf/sonar.properties

Update the following values:

sonar.jdbc.username=sonar
sonar.jdbc.password=Sonar@123
sonar.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/sonarqube

10. Configure Linux Kernel Settings

echo "vm.max_map_count=524288" | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf
echo "fs.file-max=131072" | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf

sudo sysctl -p

sudo nano /etc/security/limits.conf

Add the following lines:

sonar - nofile 131072
sonar - nproc 8192

11. Create SonarQube Service

sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/sonarqube.service

Paste the following:

[Unit]
Description=SonarQube Service
After=network.target postgresql.service

[Service]
Type=forking
User=sonar
Group=sonar
ExecStart=/opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh start
ExecStop=/opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh stop
Restart=always
LimitNOFILE=131072
LimitNPROC=8192

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

12. Reload Systemd

sudo systemctl daemon-reload

13. Enable SonarQube

sudo systemctl enable sonarqube

14. Start SonarQube

sudo systemctl start sonarqube

15. Check Status

sudo systemctl status sonarqube

16. Check Logs (if required)

sudo tail -f /opt/sonarqube/logs/sonar.log

17. Access SonarQube

http://<EC2-Public-IP>:9000

Default Login

Username: admin
Password: admin

Change the password after the first login.

Note:
- Install SonarQube Server only on this EC2 instance.
- Install SonarQube Scanner only on the Jenkins Agent.
- Open port 9000 in the EC2 Security Group.
